
[1]inconsiderate

   INCONSID'ERATE, a. [L. inconsideratus. See Consider.]

   1. Not considerate; not attending to the circumstances which regard
   safety or propriety; hasty; rash; imprudent; careless; thoughtless;
   heedless; inattentive. The young are generally inconsiderate.

   2. Proceeding from heedlessness; rash; as inconsiderate conduct.

   3. Not duly regarding; with of, before the subject; as inconsiderate of
   consequences.
